****✨ The Ultimate Guide to Prompt Writing****

A big part of getting the most out of NightCafe Studio is by getting
good at writing prompts.

That is, learning how to write for the AI in the clearest way possible.

When you do, you're much more likely to get the image result you're
imagining.

**HOW TO GENERATE RELIABLE IMAGES:**

NightCafe user ADANSITO 
was one of the first to find a general formula for more predictable
image generation.

"

**From what I've seen and experimented, it is always good to type on
this composition:**

**1. Main subject**

**2. Secondary subject**

**3. Artist names / style prompts**

**4. Photography / artistic prompts**

**5. Specific colors (optional)**

**NOTE**: The order does matter when it comes to writing prompts, so it
is better to put your main subject first in the order.

**Here's an example:** A deer passing through (

**main subject**) an abandoned neon city (

**secondary subject**), by Dan Mumford and Victo Ngai (

**artist names / styles**), 8k resolution, a masterpiece, 35mm,
hyperrealistic, hyper maximalist (

**photography/artistic prompts**), crimson, jade (

**colors**).

